lyrics:
(Verse 1)
Happy birthday, dear father, you're our rock and roll star,
Through the years, like Pink Floyd, you've shined so far.
Led Zeppelin's spirit, with a Rolling Stones vibe,
You're the Uriah Heep of our lives, forever alive.

(Chorus)
So let's sing and dance, to the tunes of your life,
With guitar solos and drum beats, removing all strife.
In this rock anthem of love, we'll raise a toast,
To the man of the hour, who rocks the most.
